# Import Aliasing

Always use the `@` path alias for imports from `src/`. Never use relative paths like `./` or `../`.

## Pattern

| ❌ Avoid | ✅ Use |
|----------|--------|
| `import App from './App'` | `import App from '@/App'` |
| `import { store } from '../store'` | `import { store } from '@/store'` |
| `import { useAppSelector } from '../../store/hooks'` | `import { useAppSelector } from '@/store/hooks'` |
| `import './index.css'` | `import '@/index.css'` |

## Rules

- Use `@/` for any import whose target lives under `src/`
- `@` maps to `src/`, so `@/store` → `src/store`, `@/components/Button` → `src/components/Button`
- Apply to `.ts`, `.tsx`, `.css`, and other importable files
